><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="flex-shrink: 0;" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">Examiné la complexité technique du déploiement osmo-epdg</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Lu. Voilà ce que j'observe :</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Le sujet réel :</strong> Déployer <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">osmo-epdg</code>
 (ePDG = Evolved Packet Data Gateway) pour VoWiFi, en Erlang/OTP, sur 
Ubuntu x86_64, intégré à un core réseau mobile existant (OsmoHLR, 
strongSwan).</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Ce que le prompt suppose déjà acquis :</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">OsmoHLR tourne (GSUP sur 4222)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">strongSwan est présent</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">L'IP de la machine est 10.0.0.1</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Les vrais problèmes techniques à résoudre :</strong></p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Erlang/OTP</strong> — quelle version est compatible avec osmo-epdg ? Ce n'est pas trivial.</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Dépendances hex.pm</strong> — <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">rebar3</code> va les télécharger, mais si pas d'internet au build, il faut un cache ou un vendor.</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Sans internet</strong> — le prompt le mentionne comme cas à gérer, c'est souvent le cas réel en labo téléco.</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Intégration CEIA ↔ strongSwan</strong> — c'est le vrai critère de succès final.</li>
</ol>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Ce que le prompt ne dit pas :</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Version d'Ubuntu (22.04 ? 24.04 ?)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Erlang/OTP déjà installé ou non</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">rebar3 disponible ou non</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Config réseau (interfaces, IKEv2...)</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Ta piste, c'est quoi exactement ?</strong>
 Tu veux produire un script bash de déploiement ? De la doc ? Ou tu 
explores d'abord l'architecture avant de coder quoi que ce soit ?</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><button type="button" data-cds="Button" class="cds-reset group/btn relative isolate inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center gap-1.5 whitespace-nowrap select-none border-0 outline-none rounded h-control font-sans text-body font-medium [&amp;:disabled:not([aria-busy])]:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none transition-shadow duration-fast focus-visible:shadow-focus text-primary aria-pressed:text-accent aspect-square w-control px-0  !text-muted hover:!text-primary" aria-label="Copier" data-testid="action-bar-copy"><span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute -z-[1] rounded-[inherit] transition-colors duration-fast group-focus-visible/btn:shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--cds-page-bg)] bg-transparent group-hover/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover group-aria-expanded/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover inset-0 group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent group-hover/btn:group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent cds-btn-squish "></span><span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 "><span class="relative"><span data-cds="Icon" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; line-height: 1; width: 1em; height: 1em; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; user-select: none; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 433.3;" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true"></span><span data-cds="Icon" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settings: 